Last Broadcast Date: Thu 24 Sep 2009
Pakistan trauma Saima in Pakistan's Swat Valley relives the trauma of events when the Pakistan army seized control of her town from Taliban militants. Peshawar-based psychiatrist Syed Muhammed Sultan tells us he's treated hundreds of patients similarly affected throughout the tribal areas. 89 Voices All this week Outlook is hearing from the twenty year olds who were born as communism crumbled in Eastern Europe in 1989. Today Ana Napiorkowska takes us on a tour of old and new in the Polish capital, Warsaw. Joel Grey Oscar winner for his role in Cabaret and now photographer, using his cell phone to produce a book of images from everyday life. Show less